## **What is an SVG Cropper?**

An **svg cropper** lets you select a bounding area and keep only what matters. Since SVG stands for Scalable Vector Graphics, you can **crop svg** content while preserving paths, shapes, and text as resolution-independent vectors.

Unlike raster tools, our **svg crop online** approach maintains perfect sharpness on every screen and print size. Use it to **crop svg image online** for UI icons, logos, charts, and illustrations.

## **Why Crop SVG Instead of PNG?**

- Keep infinite scalability without pixelation.
- Reduce file size by removing unused elements and overflow.
- Maintain editability in design tools and code.
- Improve layout consistency for web and app interfaces.
- Deliver sharper visuals on high-density displays.

When you **crop svg online**, you save time and keep your brand assets future-proof.

## **FAQ**

**Does cropping reduce quality?**

No. When you **crop svg image online**, you keep vector fidelity because paths remain mathematical descriptions, not pixels.

**Will fonts still work?**

Yes, if you embed or outline them. For maximum reliability, convert text to outlines before export if you plan to distribute widely.

**Can I batch process files?**

You can crop multiple files back to back. For automated pipelines, export each result and repeat the steps.

**What about transparency and backgrounds?**

SVG supports transparency by default. The export keeps transparent regions intact after you **crop SVG**.
